{"id": "29194", "revid": "801958", "url": "https://simple.wikipedia.org/wiki?curid=29194", "title": "Euripides", "text": "Euripides (c. 480 BC\u2013406 BC) was an Ancient Greek writer from Athens who wrote about 90 plays. Only 18 of his tragedies have survived complete, more than all other surviving ancient Greek tragedies put together. A nineteenth play, \"Rhesus\" is sometimes thought to be by Euripides, but not all classicists agree on this.\nEuripides was the last of the three greatest Ancient Greek writers of tragedies, the others being Aeschylus and Sophocles."}
